result.execSummary:
The defendant Corey D Townsend Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Corey D Townsend Jr is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Corey D Townsend Jr was found guilty of Endanger Safety/Reckless Use of Firearm Discharge Vehicle-Bldg, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(2)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of  6 YEARS with 293 days credit CONCURRENT with 15CF787 and consecutuive  to any other sentence; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 3 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 3 YEARS.
Court finds defendant IS eligible for the Challenge Incarceration program and the WI Substance Abuse program.

- No further violations rising to the level of probable cause
- Cooperate with the Probation Department

- No possession of alcohol or illegal drugs
- Random urine screens
- Seek and maintain full-time employment 
- Obtain a GED/HSED
- no contact with Shontell H and her family
- Provide a DNA sample.
